pack_align_macros(25.10)                              pack_align_macros(25.10)

Name
       pack_align_macros  -  Pushes macros (or pack of macros) to core corners
       and marks them fixed

Syntax
       pack_align_macros

       [-help]

       Pushes macros (or pack of macros) to core corners and marks them fixed.

       The pack_align_macros command executes the following two steps:

              * Aligns macros of the same size (initially placed together)  on
                the entire design.

              * Pushes  macros  (or  pack of macros) to core corners and marks
                them fixed.

       The  pack_align_macros  command   honors   the   following   rules   of
       set_macro_place_constraint.

              * Min space to macro

              * Min space to core

              * Forbidden space to macro

              * Forbidden space to core

              * Avoid abut macro edge with pins

              * Macro corner keepout

       Figure 1: Macros before running pack_align_macros

       Figure 2: Macros aligned after running pack_align_macros

       The  Figure  1  and Figure 2 show a design before and after running the
       pack_align_macros, respectively. The Figure 2 shows that the push  till
       the  core  corner  takes place when the gap between the core corner and
       the corner of the nearest macro satisfies the following  condition:

       GY <= MY  And  GX <= MX

Parameters
       None

